The luxury home has been bought by a European businessman for a record price in the Cape Town suburb. Deeds office records indicate that the house went for R51.5-million - which excluded art valued at R10-million.The property has changed hands three times since her brother, Earl Charles Spencer, sold it in 2000.The UK's Daily Mail Online reported that Diana visited the estate in January 1997.The 1100m thatch mansion, with five guest cottages and two staff homes, was sold by the Dogon Group. CEO Denise Dogon would not confirm the price, but said the sale "established a new price benchmark for the high end of the property market" in Constantia.- Additional reporting by Andr Jurgens